            [
                "<b>To the poor person, we say, etc.:</b> Meaning to say, if the court on high wants to find guilt for the poor by way of Hillel, for the rich by way of R. Elazar and for those preoccupied with [their evil] impulse by way of Yosef, there would be a fit opening for [such a] litigant to find them guilty. "
            ],
            [
                "<b>A <i>terapaik</i>:</b> A coin of the land that is a half dinar. So is it explained in Ketuvot (64a)."
            ],
            [
                "<b>They extricated him:</b> They removed the [layer] of snow from upon him.\n"
            ],
